cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel network structure for video-based action recognition using convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of off-the-shelf image-level CNNs for model parameter initialization, which suggests a possible connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of motion information, which could be related to cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper proposes a new module for pooling frame-level activations, which could be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
